cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with object recognition in natural scenes using Deep CNNs and visual attention maps computed over gaze fixations. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper mentions the application of the proposed setup in an interactive user-friendly environment for upper-limb amputees. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible sub-category as the paper mentions the use of vision to help the subject control their neuro-prosthesis. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper deals with the use of Deep CNNs for object recognition. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the use of AI techniques for object recognition in egocentric videos.
